cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper is about planning robot manipulation using a learned forward model and a model predictive path integral controller. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper explores learning methods (Gaussian Process Regression, Ensemble of Mixture Density Networks) to estimate uncertainty in the forward model. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper uses machine learning to improve robot manipulation planning. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve visual perception for the robot to locate the box and goal location. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also less likely but possible as the paper involves control of a robotic system.
